Constructor Detail

ParameterCache_mxJPO

public ParameterCache_mxJPO(matrix.db.Context _context,
                            boolean _stringLog)
                     throws Exception
Creates a new instance of the parameter cache. All default values from the parameter definitions are predefined in the parameter cache.

Parameters:
_context - MX context
_stringLog - if set to true log via string writer, false log via System.out
Throws:
Exception - if the mapping could not be initialized
See Also:
context, mapBoolean, mapList, mapMap, mapString, writer, stringWriter

ParameterCache_mxJPO

public ParameterCache_mxJPO(matrix.db.Context _context,
                            boolean _stringLog,
                            Map<String,String> _paramValues)
                     throws Exception
Creates a new instance of the parameter cache. All default values from the parameter definitions are predefined in the parameter cache.

Parameters:
_context - MX context
_stringLog - if set to true log via string writer, false log via System.out
_paramValues - predefined parameter values to set
Throws:
Exception - if the mapping could not be initialized or a predefined parameter in _paramValues is not known
See Also:
context, mapBoolean, mapList, mapMap, mapString, writer, stringWriter

ParameterCache_mxJPO

private ParameterCache_mxJPO(matrix.db.Context _context,
                             ParameterCache_mxJPO _original)
Creates a new parameter caches class used for the clone. The new parameter cache instance holds the new defined cache but all already defined value maps mapBoolean, mapList and mapString. The stringWriter is set always to null, because the writer is used for logging purpose.

Parameters:
_context - new matrix context
_original - original parameter cache class
See Also:
Object.clone(), context, mapBoolean, mapList, mapMap, mapString, stringWriter

clone

evalParameter

public int evalParameter(ParameterDef_mxJPO _paramDef,
                         String[] _args,
                         int _index)
Evaluated given parameter and defines the values for given parameter depending on the list of arguments.
  • boolean parameter: the boolean map defines for the parameter the converted value from the default value
  • list parameter: the next argument is added to the value list
  • string parameter: the next argument is defined as string value

Parameters:
_paramDef - parameter definition
_args - list of arguments from the command line
_index - current index within the list of arguments
Returns:
new index of the current index within the list of arguments
See Also:
mapBoolean, mapList, mapString
